Here’s an interesting economic question. Does inflation drive demand or will it reduce demand of consumer goods?
Consumer goods refers to a wide range of goods. Discretionary? Staples?
Not all good will be hit equally
Bottom range staples.. will be likely hit.. as people will now shift to cheaper alternatives because it is now priced outside of their comfort zone
Inflation will then have to be considered with respect to the countries demographics
Some countries with more spending power will see their middle class continuing their expenditure.. while those in countries with less than stable situations will likely cut down..

Economist statement. Inflation will make the basic goods more expensive  so the people will have to spend a larger portion of their income on the necessities  and have less spending power on discrenationaries
